This is a Python package named psitools. Install the whole thing in a virtualenv to test.
The setup.py is in the parent dir (../) of this README.

A possible route to testing, witha  virtualenv:
$ python -m venv --system-site-packages test-psitools/
$ . test-psitools/bin/acctiavte

or use the included conda specification:
$ conda env create -f STE_environment.yml
$ conda activate STE

Then install psitools, by directing pip to the location of the setup.py

$ pip install -e ~/path/to/dutstcontinuum

Bfore trying to run tests, deactivate and reactivate the virtualenv of conda env

$ deactivate
$ . test-psitools/bin/activate

or 

$ conda deactivate
$ conda activate STE

Then try pytest

$ pytest --pyargs psitools

To do the MPI tests, run under MPI. The pytest output is a bit of a mess,
but something abould eventually show up.

$ mpirun-mpich-mp -np 5 python -m pytest --pyargs psitools --with-mpi 

